Cara Operations Loses License
Cara said Days Inns has the right to set aside certain
contracts and other legal commitments under U.S. bankruptcy
laws. Atlanta-based Days Inns sought protection from
creditors under Chapter 11 of the U.S. Bankruptcy Code in
September 1991.
   Cara said the termination won't hurt its current financial
results. The Toronto food services concern acquired the
master franchise license for Canada in 1989.